---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" lang="en">
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            MEDSEN places the utmost importance on the protection of personal data,
            particularly those concerning children. This privacy policy describes
            how we collect, use, and protect your information.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            As a school health platform, we are committed to upholding the highest
            standards of security and confidentiality, in accordance with the International
            Convention on the Rights of the Child and Senegalese data protection legislation.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Data Collected</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            As part of our school health mission, we may collect:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Identification data</strong>: last name, first name, date of birth, national student identifier (INE)</li>
            <li><strong>Health data</strong>: medical assessments, vaccinations, allergies, individualized accommodation/support plans</li>
            <li><strong>Contact data</strong>: contact details of legal guardians</li>
            <li><strong>School data</strong>: school, class, grade level</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Processing Purposes</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Data is collected exclusively for the following purposes:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Ensuring student health monitoring in accordance with Article 24 of the CRC</li>
            <li>Facilitating coordination between schools and health services</li>
            <li>Enabling parents to monitor their children's health</li>
            <li>Producing anonymized statistics for school health policy management</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Health Data Protection</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Health data benefits from enhanced protection:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Encryption</strong>: all data is encrypted in transit and at rest</li>
            <li><strong>Restricted access</strong>: only authorized health professionals can access medical data</li>
            <li><strong>Traceability</strong>: every access is recorded in an audit log</li>
            <li><strong>Secure hosting</strong>: option for sovereign hosting in Senegal</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Parental Consent</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            In accordance with Article 12 of the CRC (the child's right to be heard) and the protection
            of minors:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Parental/guardian consent is required for all data processing</li>
            <li>Parents can access their children's data through the dedicated portal</li>
            <li>Consent can be withdrawn at any time</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            School health data is retained throughout the student's schooling,
            then archived in accordance with legal obligations regarding medical records.
            Data is deleted or anonymized at the end of this period.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">User Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            In accordance with applicable regulations, you have the following rights:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Right of access</strong>: obtain a copy of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong>: correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong>: request the deletion of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to object</strong>: object to the processing of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to portability</strong>: receive your data in a structured format</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Data Sharing</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Data is only shared with:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Authorized health professionals (IME doctors and nurses)</li>
            <li>Schools (non-medical data only)</li>
            <li>Health authorities (anonymized data for statistics)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-4">
            <strong>No data is sold or shared for commercial purposes.</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Security</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            MEDSEN implements appropriate technical and organizational security measures
            to protect your data against unauthorized access, modification, disclosure, or
            destruction. These measures include encryption, access controls, regular backups,
            and staff training.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            For any questions regarding this privacy policy or to exercise your rights,
            contact us at:<br />
            <a href="mailto:ndeyetalla.dioum@medsen.sn" class="text-sante-600 hover:underline">ndeyetalla.dioum@medsen.sn</a><br />
            Tel: <a href="tel:+221778458802" class="text-sante-600 hover:underline">+221 77 845 88 02</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Updates</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            This privacy policy may be updated periodically.
            The date of the last update will be indicated at the bottom of this page.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">
            Last updated: January 2026
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
